params._userAddress: The user address you want to confirm

returns._0: A boolean value indicating whether the operation was successful.

params._usersAddresses: The users addresses you want to confirm

returns._0: A boolean value indicating whether the operation was successful.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

joinIn().details: The participant must not have already registered and must pay the registration fee.

returns._0: A boolean value indicating whether the operation was successful.

pause().details: Only the account with the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE can pause the contract.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

reset().details: Only users with `DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE` can executed it.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

unpause().details: Only the account with the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE can unpause the contract.

params._newFee: The value to rewrite the current `registrationFee`

returns._0: A boolean value indicating whether the operation was successful.

confirmUserQuota(address).notice: Allow an admint o confirm a user quota.

confirmUserQuotaBatch(address[]).notice: Allow an admint o confirm a users quota.

isConfirmed(address).notice: This is the admin confirmation about the user quota

isJoined(address).notice: When an user is `joined` it's mean that the registration fee was payed and locked

joinIn().notice: Allow a participant to join in by paying the registration fee.

pause().notice: Pauses the contract, preventing any further registration.

reset().notice: Set the user related state variables to their default value.

unpause().notice: Unpauses the contract, allowing registration actions to proceed.
